(367, '_transient_846f5de80330c339e0b52d7cf2338c18', 'O:8:\"stdClass\":25:{s:4:\"name\";s:22:\"Log Deprecated Notices\";s:4:\"slug\";s:22:\"log-deprecated-notices\";s:7:\"version\";s:5:\"0.4.1\";s:6:\"author\";s:44:\"<a href=\"http://nacin.com/\">Andrew Nacin</a>\";s:14:\"author_profile\";s:36:\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/nacin\";s:8:\"requires\";s:3:\"3.0\";s:6:\"tested\";s:9:\"5.0-alpha\";s:12:\"requires_php\";b:0;s:13:\"compatibility\";a:0:{}s:6:\"rating\";d:100;s:7:\"ratings\";a:5:{i:5;i:9;i:4;i:0;i:3;i:0;i:2;i:0;i:1;i:0;}s:11:\"num_ratings\";i:9;s:15:\"support_threads\";i:1;s:24:\"support_threads_resolved\";i:0;s:10:\"downloaded\";i:93111;s:12:\"last_updated\";s:21:\"2018-07-21 1:54pm GMT\";s:5:\"added\";s:10:\"2010-06-27\";s:8:\"homepage\";s:59:\"http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/log-deprecated-notices/\";s:8:\"sections\";a:4:{s:11:\"description\";s:1453:\"<p>This plugin logs the usage of deprecated files, functions, and function arguments. It identifies where the deprecated functionality is being used and offers the alternative if available.</p>\n<p>This is a plugin for developers. WP_DEBUG is not needed, though its general usage is strongly recommended. Deprecated notices normally exposed by WP_DEBUG will be logged instead.</p>\n<p>This plugin also logs incorrect function usage, which WordPress started reporting in 3.1.</p>\n<p>Please report any bugs to plugins in a <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/support/plugin/log-deprecated-notices\" rel=\"nofollow\">support thread</a>.</p>\n<p>This is young software. It works, but there&#8217;s a lot left on the todo (check out the Other Notes tab). Have an idea? Let me know.</p>\n<h3>Ideas</h3>\n<p>These are the various things on the @todo:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Plugin identification. Also, an unobstrusive note on plugins page next to said plugins.</li>\n<li>Perhaps the ability to auto-purge the log.</li>\n<li>Ability to filter on file or plugin in which the deprecated functionality is used.</li>\n<li>Offer some kind of better multisite support.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Want to add something here? I&#8217;m all ears. plugins at <a href=\"http://andrewnacin.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">andrewnacin.com</a> or @<a href=\"http://twitter.com/nacin\" rel=\"nofollow\">nacin</a> on Twitter.</p>\n<p>I will prioritize these tasks based on feedback, so let me know what you&#8217;d like to see.</p>\n\";s:12:\"installation\";s:953:\"<p>For an automatic installation through WordPress:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Go to the &#8216;Add New&#8217; plugins screen in your WordPress admin area</li>\n<li>Search for &#8216;Log Deprecated Notices&#8217;</li>\n<li>Click &#8216;Install Now&#8217; and activate the plugin</li>\n<li>View the log in the &#8216;Tools&#8217; menu, under &#8216;Deprecated Calls&#8217;</li>\n</ol>\n<p>For a manual installation via FTP:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Upload the <code>log-deprecated-notices</code> directory to the <code>/wp-content/plugins/</code> directory</li>\n<li>Activate the plugin through the &#8216;Plugins&#8217; screen in your WordPress admin area</li>\n</ol>\n<p>To upload the plugin through WordPress, instead of FTP:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Upload the downloaded zip file on the &#8216;Add New&#8217; plugins screen (see the &#8216;Upload&#8217; tab) in your WordPress admin area and activate.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>This plugin is will remove log entries when it is uninstalled and deleted.</p>\n\";s:3:\"faq\";s:999:\"\n<h4>Installation Instructions</h4>\n<p>\n<p>For an automatic installation through WordPress:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Go to the &#8216;Add New&#8217; plugins screen in your WordPress admin area</li>\n<li>Search for &#8216;Log Deprecated Notices&#8217;</li>\n<li>Click &#8216;Install Now&#8217; and activate the plugin</li>\n<li>View the log in the &#8216;Tools&#8217; menu, under &#8216;Deprecated Calls&#8217;</li>\n</ol>\n<p>For a manual installation via FTP:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Upload the <code>log-deprecated-notices</code> directory to the <code>/wp-content/plugins/</code> directory</li>\n<li>Activate the plugin through the &#8216;Plugins&#8217; screen in your WordPress admin area</li>\n</ol>\n<p>To upload the plugin through WordPress, instead of FTP:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Upload the downloaded zip file on the &#8216;Add New&#8217; plugins screen (see the &#8216;Upload&#8217; tab) in your WordPress admin area and activate.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>This plugin is will remove log entries when it is uninstalled and deleted.</p>\n</p>\n\n\";s:11:\"screenshots\";s:229:\"<ol><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/log-deprecated-notices/trunk/screenshot-1.png?rev=1912800\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/log-deprecated-notices/trunk/screenshot-1.png?rev=1912800\" alt=\"Log screen.\"></a><p>Log screen.</p></li></ol>\";}s:13:\"download_link\";s:71:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/log-deprecated-notices.0.4.1.zip\";s:11:\"screenshots\";a:1:{i:1;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:74:\"https://ps.w.org/log-deprecated-notices/trunk/screenshot-1.png?rev=1912800\";s:7:\"caption\";s:11:\"Log screen.\";}}s:4:\"tags\";a:5:{s:5:\"admin\";s:5:\"admin\";s:10:\"deprecated\";s:10:\"deprecated\";s:8:\"e_notice\";s:8:\"E_NOTICE\";s:7:\"logging\";s:7:\"logging\";s:8:\"wp_debug\";s:8:\"WP_DEBUG\";}s:8:\"versions\";a:7:{s:7:\"0.1-RC3\";s:73:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/log-deprecated-notices.0.1-RC3.zip\";s:3:\"0.2\";s:69:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/log-deprecated-notices.0.2.zip\";s:7:\"0.2-RC1\";s:73:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/log-deprecated-notices.0.2-RC1.zip\";s:3:\"0.3\";s:69:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/log-deprecated-notices.0.3.zip\";s:3:\"0.4\";s:69:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/log-deprecated-notices.0.4.zip\";s:5:\"0.4.1\";s:71:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/log-deprecated-notices.0.4.1.zip\";s:5:\"trunk\";s:65:\"https://downloads.wordpress.org/plugin/log-deprecated-notices.zip\";}s:11:\"donate_link\";s:0:\"\";s:12:\"contributors\";a:0:{}}', 'no'),
